HEADWORD: Oneidas
<hw>O*nei"das</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Oneida</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A
tribe of Indians formerly inhabiting the region near Oneida Lake in the
State of New York, and forming part of the Five Nations. Remnants of the
tribe now live in New York, Canada, and Wisconsin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

